article.description: — Anthony Roy scored 15 points to guide New Mexico State past Seattle University 82-75 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Roy leads New Mexico State past Seattle University 82-75
article.linkText: Roy leads New Mexico State past Seattle University 82-75
article.story:
LAS CRUCES, N.M. -- — Anthony Roy scored 15 points to guide New Mexico State past Seattle University 82-75 on Saturday night.

Roy also had six rebounds for the Aggies (9-14, 2-9 Western Athletic Conference). DaJuan Gordon added 14 points and three blocks. Issa Muhammad shot 5 of 6 from the field and scored 12.

The Redhawks (16-8, 7-4) were led by Cameron Tyson with 24 points and six rebounds. Riley Grigsby added 17 points and Alex Schumacher scored 14.

NEXT UP

Both teams next play Wednesday. New Mexico State visits Grand Canyon, while Seattle U hosts Utah Tech.
